**Talint**'s client, a management consulting firm providing innovative solutions and best practices to government organizations, is a fast growing, employee focused company. Our client recently received **the Best Places to Work** in Greater Washington by the **#WashingtonBusinessJournal**.



Our client has an opening for a **Financial Operations Analyst**. This person will support the risk management and internal controls (RMIC) program at the Defense Security Cooperation Agency (DSCA). DSCA is in the discovery stage of implementing an enterprise approach to risk management across the Security Cooperation (SC) Community. The right candidate will have at least **4 years of DoD financial experience** and have a strong understanding of government accounting regulations and laws, processes, and systems**.** Must have experience with internal controls and risk management programs**.** Additionally, this person will need to have a **DoD Secret clearance**. If you do not have an active clearance, you will not be considered for the role. This role is **remote**, but there will be some ad hoc meetings that must be attended in person in the Washington DC area.



**Desired Skills and Experience:**

* DoD Secret clearance;
* Bachelor’s degree in accounting, finance, or similar;
* Must have 4 years of DoD Accounting/Financial Management;
* Knowledge of government-wide financial management policies, accounting processes, and regulations (e.g., Treasury Financial Manuals (TFMs), OMB Circulars, and Federal Accounting Standards Advisory Board (FASAB) standards);
* Experience with compliance, risk, and control processes and frameworks, including the COSO frameworks;
* Prepare management plans, reports, and presentations for customer programs and executive management;
* Strong critical thinking and analysis, planning, and problem-solving skills;
* Advanced verbal and written communication ability.


**Why our client?**

* Competitive total compensation and benefits package that includes health, retirement, and paid time off;
* Our client fosters an open-door policy between employees and leadership to ensure direct lines of communication;
* Incredible opportunities for advancement as they continue to grow;
* They understand the importance of striking a work/life balance and offers flexible schedules.


**Responsibilities:**

* Support the DSCA in sustaining their RMIC program;
* Work closely with DSCA’s process owners to document processes, identify risk and controls, and perform assessments;
* Compile and deliver the yearly Statement of Assurance (SOA);
* Collaborating with SC community, documenting approach, implementation, and execution.
* Support the coordination and maintenance of DSCA compliance, risk, and control programs.

Description:The Dallas Symphony Association has an immediate opportunity for an experienced, detail-oriented Budgeting & Financial Analyst. The primary responsibilities of this vital position include leading the annual budget process, preparing updated financial forecasts throughout the year, ensuring budget compliance for all departments, and preparing variance analyses and explanations. 




Other duties include (but are not limited to):

* Assisting Controller and Chief Financial Officer with special projects;
* Assisting with the close of monthly financial statements and preparation of Board financial packages;
* Providing financial information for grant requests;
* Performing account reconciliations and reviewing accounts payable coding;
* Acting as the administrator for the Sage APA online accounts payable system;
* Assisting with the annual audit process as required;
* Creating event codes in Intacct accounting system for new DSP concerts;
* Providing support to the individual departments for coding, questions, etc.;
* Working with the Meyerson staff to track the third-party events and rentals;
* Reviewing payroll general ledger files before importing to accounting system;
* Implementing and providing analysis on statistical metrics, number of tickets sold, average ticket price, and more to be determined.

The Dallas Symphony provides excellent benefits, free parking, and tickets when available. No phone calls, please.




